Consider the following AWS IAM policy definition for an S3 bucket:
{
  "Version": "2012-10-17",
  "Statement": [
    {
      "Sid": "RuleA",
      "Effect": "Allow",
      "Action": ["s3:PutObject"],
      "Resource": ["arn:aws:s3:::customer-identity-keys/*"]
    },
    {
      "Sid": "RuleB",
      "Effect": "Deny",
      "Action": ["s3:PutObject"],
      "Resource": ["arn:aws:s3:::customer-identity-keys/confidential/*"]
    }
  ]
}
If an IAM role containing this policy attempts to make an API call to 's3:PutObject' on target file 'arn:aws:s3:::customer-identity-keys/public-docs/secret.keys', what is the final decision outcome under AWS policy evaluation logic?

